div.p: Each domain (SC, FIN, OTC) has its own isolated Power BI repository with dev and main branches, along with dedicated build and release pipelines. All pipelines authenticate to Power BI through a single Service Connection, which securely stores our Service Principal (SPN) credentials.

The build pipeline generates packaged PBIP artifacts and publishes them to an Azure Artifact Feed for each domain. The release pipeline retrieves these artifacts and deploys them to the corresponding Power BI workspaces (Dev Prod), using REST API and XMLA endpoints.
A central repository holds all shared build/release scripts so they can be reused across every domain, ensuring consistency and reducing duplication.

Each domain requires at least one designated Release Manager (or approver).
This person is responsible for validating the changes and approving the release pipeline stage gates.
The role does not require a separate job title any domain expert or Power BI workspace admin may act as the Release Manager.
The Release Manager ensures that only validated and approved PBIP changes are promoted from Dev Test Prod.
